description: A single folio from a music manuscript, now in a collection of fragments. Currently numbered f. 20, but the original folio number XVII remains at the top of the recto side of the fragment. Contains fragments of two polyphonic (apparently 4-part) settings: Viderunt omnes … Salutare Dei nostri and Alleluia! Dies sanctificatus. There were likely additional voice parts on facing pages. The two settings apparently share a common Alleluia, since the lower voices of the Alleluia on the recto side fit with the upper voices of that on the verso.
